(Metrology helper: take three Z probe samples)

(Run from MDI:)
(  o<probe_z_three_samples> call)

(Purpose:)
(  Touch the same surface three times and print each measured MACHINE Z)
(  height. This is useful for manually tabulating homing/probing)
(  repeatability data.)

(Assumptions before running:)
(  1. Click Probe Basic "UPDATE PROBE PARAMS" first.)
(  2. Probe tool is loaded; #3014 must match the current tool.)
(  3. Start above the test surface within max Z distance #3020.)
(  4. Units are machine units from the active LinuxCNC config, mm here.)

(Behavior:)
(  - Forces probe measure-only mode with #3030 = 1.)
(  - Does not set or rewrite WCO Z.)
(  - Calls probe_z_minus_sub.ngc three times.)
(  - Reports exactly one DEBUG value per hit: measured MACHINE Z.)
(  - Restores the prior #3030 value before exiting.)

o<probe_z_three_samples> sub

  (Force measure-only mode so this does not set WCO Z)
  #<saved_probe_mode> = #3030
  #3030 = 1

  (Active WCS Z offset; G92 is canceled inside probe_z_minus_sub)
  #<workspace_z> = #[5203 + [20 * #5220]]

  #<sample> = 1
  o100 while [#<sample> LE 3]
    o<probe_z_minus_sub> call [#3014][#3015][#3016][#3017][#3020][#3021][#3030]

    (probe_z_minus_sub publishes the measured WCS Z position to #1009)
    #<machine_z> = [#1009 + #<workspace_z>]
    (DEBUG, Z PROBE SAMPLE #<sample> = #<machine_z>)

    #<sample> = [#<sample> + 1]
  o100 endwhile

  #3030 = #<saved_probe_mode>

o<probe_z_three_samples> endsub

M2
